us.ihmc.euclid.exceptions

Class SingularMatrixException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • java.lang.RuntimeException
          • us.ihmc.euclid.exceptions.SingularMatrixException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class SingularMatrixException
extends java.lang.RuntimeException
    RuntimeException dedicated to operations where a matrix needs to be inverted. Typically, this corresponds to when a matrix is singular, i.e. its determinant is equal to zero, making impossible to compute its inverse.
